  "text": "Similarly, GLFY could not move laterally within the same tissue layer (Fig. 5C,F) . We have previously found that periclinal, as well as anticlinal, sectors of LFY can rescue mutant parts of flowers, indicating that LFY moves in both directions [CITATION_1] . One possibility for the apparently different behavior of LFY and GLFY is that the greater size of GLFY, compared with endogenous LFY, reduces its ability to move laterally within tissue layers.",
